      • concat

        public static java.lang.String concat(java.lang.Object[] arr,
                                      java.lang.String filler)
        Concatenates all objects in the array with the given filler. Example:

        ArrayUtils.concat(new String[] {"Hello", "world!", "How", "are", "you?"}, "_");

        Would return "Hello_world!_How_are_you?"
        Parameters:
        arr - the array
        filler - the String to concatenate the objects with
        Returns:
        The concatenated String
